Estimations (Part A)

The general model for estimation is as follows:

\[\begin{align*} \text{ln } p_{ijk} &= \alpha + \beta DIG_i + \gamma_1 \rho_k + \gamma_2 \theta_{ij} + \gamma_3 tariff_{ijk} \\ & + \gamma_4 NTM_{ijk}^{Tech} + \gamma_5 NTM_{ijk}^{Non-Tech} + \gamma_{6i}(NTM_{ijk}^{Tech} \times \delta_i) + \gamma_{7i}(NTM_{ijk}^{Non-Tech} \times \delta_i) \\ & + \gamma_8 regsim_{ij} + \epsilon_{ijk} \end{align*}\]

where

\(DIG_i\) is the average score of separate Pillar measures capturing digital-trade regulation imposed by country \(i\) on all imports
\(\rho\) is the HS6 product fixed effects dummy variable (since regressions are estimated at chapter-level (i.e. there are 96 separate regressions)
\(\theta\) is the pair characteristics (i.e. distance, contiguity, landlocked status, common language, and RTA)
\(tariff_{ijk}\) is the applied tariff (MFN or lowest preferential, if available) imposed by \(i\) on imports of product \(k\) from \(j\)
\(NTM_{ijk}^{Tech}\) is the count of separate non-tariff measures from chapters A to C imposed by \(i\) on imports of product \(k\) from \(j\)
\(NTM_{ijk}^{Non-Tech}\) is the count of separate non-tariff measures from chapters D to O imposed by \(i\) on imports of product \(k\) from \(j\)
\(regsim_{ij}\) is a measure of regulatory similarity of country \(i\) and \(j\)
\(\delta_{i}\) is fixed effect of country \(i\) (included for interaction with \(NTM\))

Model 1 (only RDTII & product fixed-effects)

\[\begin{align*} \text{ln } p_{ijk} &= \alpha + \beta DIG_i + \gamma_2 \rho_k + \epsilon_{ijk} \end{align*}\]
